{
  "texts": [
    "The choice of embedding neural network is surprisingly unimportantour testing indicated that using a small network provided adequate context retrieval, and using a larger, more computationally intensive network did not provide significant benefits.Once document chunks are embedded into the vector space, the final component of a RAG architecture is a database, which stores the vectors for efficient retrieval.",
    "Although it is possible to create a custom database for this purpose, several excellent, open-source databases exist.",
    "We have used ChromaDB in our work [10].",
    "In the Fall 2023 semester, staff in the Electrical and Computer Engineering (ECE) department at the University of Waterloo created a chatbot named Oliver for course-aligned assistance and deployed it into two courses as a pilot project.Oliver consists of a web server, originally Nginx but now Apache, a web backend using Django, a RAG database using ChromaDB, and a front-end webpage for user interaction.",
    "It is shown in Figure 1."
  ]
}